The  Federal Reserve  bought $2.522
billion of  Treasuries (TREFTOTL)  after rescheduling the purchases earlier
today due to technical difficulties.  Securities maturing from February 2036 to November 2041
were acquired, the New York Fed said in a  statement . The
purchases are part of the Fedâ€™s maturity extension program,
known as Operation Twist.  The Federal  Reserve Bank  of New York rescheduled an initial
